I never liked any theoretical CS courses, but what I found hideous in the first place turned out to be a blessing in the end.  Levesque made the course easy by giving clear and excellent explanations.  Assignments were difficult (but the fair marking made up for it), but the quizzies, midterm and the final were all very straight-forward.  I'm thoroughly satisfied with this prof and I'm looking forward to taking his courses again.
